<Author>Emma4995
<Content>Vey good for the money paid! Ive never had a very good impression on Barcelona, when i think Barcelonai think of drunken Brits on hen and stag do's!!But how wrong was i!!Barcelona IS one of the most beautiful places i have ever been to with so much culture, i could not decide what to see first...Overview of our trip..Hotel Espana,,,This hotel is very cheap to stay at and with a 2* rating i was very concerned to what the quality of the room would be like...But i was pleasently surprised, first the hotel staff are freindly breakfast good and rooms very clean, BASIC but comfortable!!Would reccomend this hotel for the pure fact of its location right in the centre of the Rambla!! which in my eyes the best part of Barcelona, a long street leading to the harbour with resturants and spainish dressed up in all sorts trying to entertain you along the way, a must see!!From the airport:taxi or bus to centre then i advise popping into tourist informaton which is next to bus stop and they will give you directions to your hotel which is a 10 min walk, My advise:For 26 euros you can have a two day unlimited pass on the open top tourist bus which is well worth the money, this bus goes all round Barcelona stopping off at various tourist stops including olympic stadium, beach, harbour, port, aqauriam, barcelona football stadium (nou camp) cathedrals, shopping centres, zoo ect ect this bus allows you to hop on hop off as much as you like and with buses every 6 min you are never waiting long for the next to arrive , a must to see all the beautiful spots of barcelona,Enjoy your holiday i certainly did!! xxxxxxxxx will add photos shortly 
