<Author>strawberrycheesecake
<Content>Suited us fine! After hearing all the bad reviews about this hotel, i was a little concerned about staying here but it was absolutely fine and it is a fantastic value hotel.The reception staff are very friendly, polite and speak good english and there are two computers in reception with internet connection. My first impressions of the hotel were very good, the decor and old design of the hotel make it look very appealing, the rooms however are much more basic- but we only wanted a place to sleep!We arrived in the day time and i was a little worried about walking back to this hotel at night, only because it is a side street but we had no trouble and there are plenty of people bustling up and down the side street and it is very well lit, so it was fine.The rooms are very basic and the shower could of done with updating but it was fine and very clean. The air con was good and the bed was comfortable with plenty of towels. The only concern that i had is that the door to the hotel room was old and i wasnt sure how much the lock could withstand if someone wanted to break in. For precaution sake, we would leave out tv and light on when we went out at night- we had no problems! There are safes available in the reception however, so we could of used these.Breakfast was very basic but nice and plentiful and enough to start you off in the morning. We never had an evening meal in the hotel but the restaurant seemed very popular both with people staying in the hotel and people coming in from outside.The most fantastic thing about this hotel is the location. It is literally just off of La Ramblas, enough to be near but not enough to be noisy. There is a Metro stop a minutes walk away and it is close to the harbour, the gothic area and great nightlife area, with bars, restaurants and outdoor cafes on las ramblas.The hotel is easy to find, simply take the A1 bus to Placa Catalunya, then either walk down La Ramblas or take the metro to Liceu and then the hotel is a minutes walk down a diagonal side street. The hotel seemed very popular with a mix of people, business men, school groups, young and old couples... 
