<Content>Had a Great Time Here !!!! Myself and my partner (both in our 30's) stayed here 17th Dec 06 for 3 nights, I feel I have to post a review as we never experienced ANY of the problems people have wrote here. The breakfast was nice, a good selection. The reception staff were ALL lovely and helpful in giving us directions (in paricular to the Nou Camp Stadium, which is a must) or answering any questions.The hotel itself is lovely, the rooms basic, (well we did go just to sleep and wash there) . It is a very good base to stay at, in an ideal location (right in the centre of Las Ramblas with 2 train stations on the doorstep).Our ONLY and Very MINOR problem was that we had forgotten our little alarm clock and when we asked for a 6am call, (to catch a train to go sightseeing) we were informed the telephone connection in our allocated room was broken, and at that time in the morning when the breakfast staff are arriving, we could not be guaranteed a knock on the door, (which we never got) good job we woke up anyway.As with any place (even at home), you get groups gathering on corners, which was not a problem for us, as we thought we were lost on our first night ,and ended up having a laugh and joke with a group of lads and girls, (on a street corner) when we asked for directions because we were facing our street. (we did not know where we were) haha.Hope this helps with your decision in going to this hotel.We did not pay much, so we got what we paid for (cheap an cheerful, with every amenity (what we needed) PLUS more than what we expected (after reading all these other reviews).All in all u get what u pay for in life, so when it does not cost you much (or is extremely cheap, or a bargain) it normally is, SO do NOT expect THE RITZ.They are trying to do their best.AND their best was what we needed in a city at that time ( a week before Christmas).It was good for shopping.Reviews 
