<Content>What A Nightmare!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Where do I begin? I am very disappointed to say the least. Our 鈥榣ong weekend鈥?break turned out to be the holiday from hell!Initially we (me and my girlfriend) were about to cancel due to the terrible reviews of thefts, rude staff, noise, etc. However, having spoke to our travel representative we were assured all would be ok.During our first day there were some strange occurrences in our room on our return after having been out for a meal e.g. we found hairs in the bath that didn鈥檛 belong to either of us, footprints in the bathroom, open windows, etc. We didn鈥檛 report the incidents as none of our belongings had been tampered with or stolen. As a precautionary measure we decided to get a safe for peace of mind.All seemed well until our return to the hotel on the second night. After a night out me and my girlfriend inadvertently realized that misplaced the room key. Upon asking for a spare at reception we were asked our room number. When we confirmed our room number we were welcomed with what I can only describe a tirade of verbal abuse. The gentleman at reception in broken English said we must leave immediately! Obviously we were very confused. When we asked why we were told that it was due to excessive noise coming from our room. He was not in the slightest interested in the fact that we had been out all night and the noise must have been coming from one of the adjoining rooms 鈥?not ours! He kept on shouting 鈥測ou must leave鈥?鈥測ou must leave鈥? We decided to leave (in hindsight we should have stayed and called the police) and resolve the issue by speaking to the manager first thing the following morning. As a consequence we found ourselves trawling the streets with our entire luggage in the early hours of the morning. To make matters worse the neighborhood was what I can only describe as very dangerous. At one point we were being followed by 4 men. Eventually we found a hotel (Hotel Mileni) costing 拢90 per night. We had no choice but to accept. Needless to say my girlfriend was terrified by the whole experience.The next morning we went back to Hotel Espana in order to speak to the manager in order to obtain an explanation. We were told the manager was unavailable (even via phone). It was a different person on reception. He too told us the level of noise was unacceptable. He was totally disinterested in the fact that we were out and we were receiving the blame unnecessarily.We decided had no option than to report to the police. After waiting for an hour to be seen we were redirected to another police station. At the second police station we were told that it was not a police matter as any theft or violence had not occurred. We went back to Hotel Espana requesting a refund, we were told to take it up with our travel agent. This wasted almost an entire day in our 3 day trip! We had no choice other than to check back into the hotel where we had spent the previous night.All the above said Barcelona is a beautiful city and we would definitely visit again 鈥?but not stay at Esapana hotel! 
