<Content>A great hotel in need of refurbishment We travelled to Barcelona in September 2006 and stayed in this lovely old hotel built in 1900. Unfortunately many of the rooms have not been re-furbished since we guessed the 1950s. Our first room was on a beautiful but vertigo inducing landing (see photo). This had a bare striplight and switch in the bathroom - very dangerous! We asked to move and were given a much better room in a refurbished (1980s) part of the hotel which was much better.Overall the rooms were clean and tidy,with no evidence of the cockroaches or noise mentioned by others in their reviews. We would, however, not go there again, preferring to spend a few more euros for something better. This is definitely a LOW BUDGET HOTEL. The area is fine being next to the Liceu opera house and right in the centre of the Ramblas - the best street in Barcelona. But beware rampant pickpocketing. We had a purse stolen from a handbag - luckily containing only 35 euros.Tip: on your first day buy a Bus Touristic ticket. This hop-on hop-off service goes to every site of interest every few minutes. A bargain.Prices are high in the main tourist streets: 2 cokes=13 euros! But take one step off the main Ramblas and prices halve and quality goes up. Our best restaurant was La Fonda, Carrer dels Escudellers just off the Ramblas - 30 euros for 2 people, 2 courses, wine, coffee - stunning food, brilliantly cooked with well judged sauces. Smaller bars provided good fresh lunches for 15 euros for 2.Good trip! 
