<Content>Quaint hotel It was our silver wedding anniversary and as we are not into parties we decided to go on a weekend break to Barcelona. I booked a city break with flyglobespan and chose the Espana as our hotel. After reading all the previous comments prior to our visit last weekend, we were a bit apprehensive. It didn't auger well when we first saw the hotel down a side street from Las Ramblas, but as soon as we set foot inside the front door we knew we'd made the right choice. The foyer and dining rooms were a throwback to it's obviously better days but were still very impressive. Our room on the 3rd floor looked onto an inner courtyard and was very peaceful, just as we wanted. The room was spotless, as was the bathroom. Clean bed linen and towels on both days we were there. The continental buffet breakfast was self service and set you up for a heavy days sightseeing. The staff were very friendly and helpful and I can't think of anything bad to say against it. It's location is very central and has good access to Las Ramblas (a must see!) and also Playa Catalunya where the tour buses leave from. The airport bus also leaves from here and you can catch a train to the airport as well.My wife and I agreed that we will definitely go back to Barcelona for a short break (3 days is long enough in a city that hardly ever sleeps!) and that the Espana hotel will be where we will be staying. 
