<Author>Barcelonalover
<Content>Great value in the winter !!! I always stay at Hotel Espana during January, because of their promotional rate during low season... in fact I am flying tomorrow and look forward to it. I find it too pricey in the summer 100 EUR inkl. breakfast. During high season I stay at Hostal Opera which is just across Hotel Espana. They have the same rate of 55 EUR for a double all year round, but I would only recommend it in the summer because of their location and price. But in the winter you find better deals with Hotels.The double is 50 EUR excl. breakfast during low season. Search the internet for deals. If you book directly through the hotel, they offer 65 EUR inkl breakfast. Dont take advantage of the breakfast they offer, it is not good (all prepackaged). You can get a coffee and croissant every where else for 2.50 eur. But thats the only negative thing that I can say about this hotel.Top Hotel floor is used by students who study in Barcelona. So I recommend that you ask for an exterior room on the first or second floor. But keep in mind two things: Barcelona is a bit noisy, this is just something that you must accept. And walls are thin. Also interior rooms maybe quiter, but I would never opt for it, because they are dark!!!Rooms are charming and clean, bath room is very spacious, which you dont find often in Barcelona.Staff is friendly and speaks English. Night staff does not, but this is not a problem.They have an excellent restaurant, you just never see too many people in there.But the biggest advantage is the location!!!! There is not better one. You are right where you want to be (Las Ramblas and Boqueria market, across the Gothic Quarter and main shopping area) and still in a quieter side street. In the back is El Raval, which looks a bit seedy, but they are slowly cleaning it up and already is very hip with many bars. However, at night I would suggest that you never walk alone. Also, watch your purse, especially in the summer this is a big problem!!!! Be aware near the Picasso Museum, many many signs that say Beware pickpockets. If you keep your eyes open, you can easily spot the guys who want to snatch your camera or money.I like Barcelona in January, nice weather (15-17 Celsius) and it is not as crowded as in the summer. Also they have the winter sale. 
